ass="entry-content"><p>In China, the greatest astronomer of the Middle Kingdom was Tcheou Kong, the brother of Emperor Wou Wang who lived in the eleventh century before our era. He built an observatory in the city of Honan-fu, determined the position of the solstices, discovered the latitude, and deduced the inclination of the axis of the Earth &hellip;</p></div><div class="entry-footer"><div class="entry-footer-top"> <a href="http://sweetlantern.com/the-great-civilizations/" title="The Great Civilizations" class="entry-button">Continue Reading</a></div><div class="entry-footer-bottom"><div class="entry-share"><ul><li><a href="https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=http://sweetlantern.com/the-great-civilizations/" onclick="window.open(this.href, 'facebook-share','width=580,height=296');return false;"><span class="fa fa-facebook"></span></a></li><li><a href="http://twitter.com/share?text=The%20Great%20Civilizations&#038;url=http://sweetlantern.com/the-great-civilizations/" onclick="window.open(this.href, 'twitter-share', 'width=550,height=235');return false;"><span class="fa fa-twitter"></span></a></li><li><a href="#" onclick="window.open('http://pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=http://sweetlantern.com/the-great-civilizations/&#038;media=http://sweetlantern.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/mezzanine_288.jpg.resize.800x450.jpg&#038;description=The%20Great%20Civilizations', 'pinterest-share', 'width=490,height=530');return false;"><span class="fa fa-pinterest-p"></span></a></li><li><a href="https://plus.google.com/share?url=http://sweetlantern.com/the-great-civilizations/" onclick="window.open(this.href, 'google-plus-share', 'width=490,height=530');return false;"><span class="fa fa-google-plus"></span></a></li></ul></div><div class="entry-comments"> <a href="http://sweetlantern.com/the-great-civilizations/#comments"><span class="fa fa-comment"></span> <span class="comments-counting">190</span> </a></div></div></div></div></div></article><article id="entry-64" class="post-64 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-astronomy tag-astronomy entry entry-center"style="text-align:center;"><div class="entry-row"><div class="entry-full-center"><div class="entry-header"><div class="entry-meta"> <span class="entry-cat"><a href="http://sweetlantern.com/category/astronomy/" rel="category tag">Astronomy</a></span></div><h2 class="entry-title"><a href="http://sweetlantern.com/where-to-study-astronomy-and-space-sciences/">Where to Study Astronomy and Space Sciences?</a></h2><div class="entry-meta"> <span class="entry-author">By <a href="http://sweetlantern.com/author/Enigma/" title="Posts by Enigma" rel="author">Enigma</a> </span> <span class="entry-date">on <a href="http://sweetlantern.com/2017/12/">Saturday, December 2, 2017</a></span></div></div><div  class="entry-media" > <a href="http://sweetlantern.com/where-to-study-astronomy-and-space-sciences/" class="entry-thumb" title="Permalink to: &quot;Where to Study Astronomy and Space Sciences?&quot;"><img width="780" height="381" src="http://sweetlantern.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/West-Bengal-State-780x381.jpg" class="attachment-WRT-post-image size-WRT-post-image wp-post-image" alt="" srcset="http://sweetlantern.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/West-Bengal-State-780x381.jpg 780w, http://sweetlantern.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/West-Bengal-State-300x146.jpg 300w, http://sweetlantern.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/West-Bengal-State-768x375.jpg 768w, http://sweetlantern.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/West-Bengal-State.jpg 883w" sizes="(max-width: 780px) 100vw, 780px" /></a></div><div class="entry-content"><p>Most astronomy positions require a Ph.D. in the field of astronomy, which usually takes 5-7 years to complete. These programs are likely to contain courses in astrophysics, stellar and planetary physics, galaxies, cosmology, interstellar medium and optics.</p></div><div class="entry-footer"><div class="entry-footer-top"> <a href="http://swee